<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="60" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1826,2031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1826,1851]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body elongate, arenicoliform. Prostomium T-shaped with lateral horns. Peristomium achaetous, surrounding prostomium dorsally and forming upper and lower lips of mouth ventrally. Parapodia of posterior segments with dorsal and ventral cirri; interramal 
<taxonomicName box="[722,798,1898,1923]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Pseudoscalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="papilla">papilla</taxonomicName>
present; postsetal lamellae absent. Branchiae present in anterior segments. Setae include capillaries, lyrate setae, and sometimes inconspicuous blunt, pointed, or bifurcated spinous setae anterior to capillaries of setigers 
<number box="[671,685,1971,1995]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
or 
<number box="[721,765,1971,1995]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1â€’2</number>
, representing homologues of lyrate setae; large conspicuous acicular spines absent. Pygidium with long anal cirri.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="61" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Remarks.</emphasis>
Until recently, 
<taxonomicName box="[491,732,151,176]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="inflatum">
<emphasis box="[491,732,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Scalibregma inflatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered to be cosmopolitan in its distribution. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mackie" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Mackie, A. S. Y. (1991) Scalibregma celticum new species (Polychaeta, Scalibregmatidae) from Europe, with a redescription of Scalibregma inflatum Rathke, 1843 and comments on the genus Sclerobregma Hartman, 1965. Bulletin of Marine Science, 48, 268 - 276." type="journal article" year="1991">
Mackie (
<number box="[159,219,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, however, demonstrated sufficient variability in European populations to define an additional, closely related species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mackie, 1991" authorityName="Mackie" authorityYear="1991" box="[329,617,223,248]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="celticum">
<emphasis box="[329,452,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">S. celticum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mackie" box="[460,617,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Mackie, A. S. Y. (1991) Scalibregma celticum new species (Polychaeta, Scalibregmatidae) from Europe, with a redescription of Scalibregma inflatum Rathke, 1843 and comments on the genus Sclerobregma Hartman, 1965. Bulletin of Marine Science, 48, 268 - 276." type="journal article" year="1991">
Mackie, 
<number box="[558,617,224,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Among other observations, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mackie" box="[941,1106,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Mackie, A. S. Y. (1991) Scalibregma celticum new species (Polychaeta, Scalibregmatidae) from Europe, with a redescription of Scalibregma inflatum Rathke, 1843 and comments on the genus Sclerobregma Hartman, 1965. Bulletin of Marine Science, 48, 268 - 276." type="journal article" year="1991">
Mackie (
<number box="[1040,1098,224,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
discovered that short slender spines were present anterior to the capillaries of a few anterior noto- and neuropodia anterior to the setigers where lyrate setae occurred. Prior to this study 
<taxonomicName box="[619,760,295,320]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[619,760,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Scalibregma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been defined as lacking any 
<typeStatus box="[1148,1196,296,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">type</typeStatus>
of spinous seta. The spinous setae discovered by Mackie were not the large, curved acicular spines that have been reported for species of 
<emphasis box="[197,959,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName box="[197,364,367,392]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Asclerocheilus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Asclerocheilus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[392,543,367,392]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Oligobregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Oligobregma</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[571,774,367,392]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Parasclerocheilus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Parasclerocheilus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[797,955,367,392]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Sclerobregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Sclerobregma</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1046,1196,367,392]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Sclerocheilus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1046,1196,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Sclerocheilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but were instead inconspicuous companions of the capillaries. For 
<taxonomicName authority="Mackie (1991)" authorityName="Mackie" authorityYear="1991" box="[717,1016,404,429]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="inflatum">
<emphasis box="[717,840,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">S. inflatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mackie" box="[849,1016,404,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Mackie, A. S. Y. (1991) Scalibregma celticum new species (Polychaeta, Scalibregmatidae) from Europe, with a redescription of Scalibregma inflatum Rathke, 1843 and comments on the genus Sclerobregma Hartman, 1965. Bulletin of Marine Science, 48, 268 - 276." type="journal article" year="1991">
Mackie (
<number box="[950,1008,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
found that some of these setae were forked or split on their tips. This observation plus their position in the setal fascicles suggested that they were homologous to the lyrate setae of following segments. Mackie further suggested that the larger recurved spines of other genera were homologous with capillaries.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
<bibRefCitation author="Mackie" box="[199,364,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Mackie, A. S. Y. (1991) Scalibregma celticum new species (Polychaeta, Scalibregmatidae) from Europe, with a redescription of Scalibregma inflatum Rathke, 1843 and comments on the genus Sclerobregma Hartman, 1965. Bulletin of Marine Science, 48, 268 - 276." type="journal article" year="1991">
Mackie (
<number box="[298,356,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
redescribed 
<taxonomicName box="[507,747,548,573]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="inflatum">
<emphasis box="[507,747,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Scalibregma inflatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on specimens from the 
<typeStatus box="[1086,1134,549,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[1260,1350,549,573]" name="Norway" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Norway</collectingCountry>
as well as from 
<collectingCountry box="[248,340,583,608]" name="Sweden" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Sweden</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[353,454,583,608]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Scotland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[468,539,583,608]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Wales</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[603,686,583,608]" name="Ireland" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Ireland</collectingCountry>
. The second species, 
<taxonomicName box="[937,1062,583,608]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="celticum">
<emphasis box="[937,1062,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">S. celticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was from 
<collectingCountry box="[1196,1297,583,608]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Scotland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1311,1382,583,608]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Wales</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,227,621,644]" name="France" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">France</collectingCountry>
and differed in that the small spinous setae of setigers 
<number box="[922,964,620,644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1â€’2</number>
were blunt-tipped instead of bifurcate. Additionally, eyes were present instead of absent and there were differences in the form of the peristomium, size and distribution of the epidermal pads above the notopodia, and in the number and arrangement of the pygidial cirri. 
<taxonomicName box="[212,334,727,752]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="celticum">
<emphasis box="[212,334,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">S. celticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was subsequently reported from the Mediterranean by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cinar" box="[953,1097,727,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Cinar, M. H. (2005) Polychaetes from the coast of northern Cyprus (eastern Mediterranean Sea), with two new records for the Mediterranean Sea. Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 46, 143 - 159." type="journal article" year="2005">
Ã‡inar (
<number box="[1030,1089,727,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[1151,1377,727,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Lomiri, S., Vani, D., Tomassetti, P., Trabucco, B., Maggi, C., &amp; Nonnis, O. (2012) First record of Scalibregma celticum (Annelida: Polychaeta: Scalibregmatidae) in Italian marine waters. Marine Biodiversity Records, 5, 1 - 4. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1017 / S 175526721100100 X" type="journal article">
Lomiri 
<emphasis box="[1236,1292,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[1307,1369,728,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
<bibRefCitation author="Mackie" box="[199,364,764,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Mackie, A. S. Y. (1991) Scalibregma celticum new species (Polychaeta, Scalibregmatidae) from Europe, with a redescription of Scalibregma inflatum Rathke, 1843 and comments on the genus Sclerobregma Hartman, 1965. Bulletin of Marine Science, 48, 268 - 276." type="journal article" year="1991">
Mackie (
<number box="[298,356,764,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
also re-examined 
<taxonomicName authority="Bertelsen &amp; Weston, 1980" authorityName="Bertelsen &amp; Weston" authorityYear="1980" box="[568,1162,764,789]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Sclerobregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="stenocerum">
<emphasis box="[568,859,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Sclerobregma stenocerum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bertelsen" box="[866,1162,764,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Bertelsen, R. D. &amp; Weston, D. P. (1980) A new species of Sclerobregma (Polychaeta: Scalibregmatidae) from off the southeastern United States. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 93, 708 - 713. Available from: http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 107589 (Accessed 19 Oct. 2015)" type="journal article" year="1980">
Bertelsen &amp; Weston, 
<number box="[1103,1162,764,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from shelf depths along the southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[342,494,799,824]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">United States</collectingCountry>
and found that the anterior acicular spines reported for the species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bertelsen" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Bertelsen, R. D. &amp; Weston, D. P. (1980) A new species of Sclerobregma (Polychaeta: Scalibregmatidae) from off the southeastern United States. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 93, 708 - 713. Available from: http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 107589 (Accessed 19 Oct. 2015)" type="journal article" year="1980">
Bertelsen &amp; Weston (
<number box="[252,310,836,860]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1980.0">1980</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
were of the small, inconspicuous kind found in 
<taxonomicName box="[881,1022,836,861]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[881,1022,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Scalibregma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species instead of the large, curved acicular spines found on other species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[677,832,871,896]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Sclerobregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[677,832,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Sclerobregma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[849,1009,872,896]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Sclerobregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="stenocerum">
<emphasis box="[849,1009,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">S. stenocerum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was therefore transferred by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mackie" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Mackie, A. S. Y. (1991) Scalibregma celticum new species (Polychaeta, Scalibregmatidae) from Europe, with a redescription of Scalibregma inflatum Rathke, 1843 and comments on the genus Sclerobregma Hartman, 1965. Bulletin of Marine Science, 48, 268 - 276." type="journal article" year="1991">
Mackie (
<number box="[159,217,908,932]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[263,403,908,933]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[263,403,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Scalibregma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Mackie also examined the 
<typeStatus box="[723,821,908,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartman, 1965" authorityName="Hartman" authorityYear="1965" box="[860,1212,908,933]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="branchiatum">
<emphasis box="[860,1032,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">S. branchiatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hartman" box="[1040,1212,908,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Hartman, O. (1965) Deep-water benthic polychaetous annelids off New England to Bermuda and other North Atlantic areas. Allan Hancock Foundation Publications Occasional Paper, 28, 1 - 378." type="journal article" year="1965">
Hartman, 
<number box="[1153,1212,908,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1965.0">1965</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the type-species of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,306,943,968]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Sclerobregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,306,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Sclerobregma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from deep water in the western North Atlantic and found short spinous setae anterior to the larger acicular spines of setigers 
<number box="[467,481,980,1004]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number box="[545,562,980,1004]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2.0">2</number>
. A similar situation exists in 
<taxonomicName authority="Blake, 1972" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1972" box="[918,1432,980,1005]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Cryptosclerocheilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Incertae sedis" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="baffinensis">
<emphasis box="[918,1277,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Cryptosclerocheilus baffinensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Blake" box="[1289,1432,980,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Blake, J. A. (1972) Two new species of polychaetous annelid worms from Baffin Bay and the Davis Strait. Bulletin of the Southern California Academy of Sciences, 71, 127 - 132. Available from: http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 106891 (Accessed 19 Oct. 2015)" type="journal article" year="1972">
Blake, 
<number box="[1373,1432,980,1004]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1972.0">1972</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from deep water in Baffin Bay. This species was reported to have slender, blunt-tipped spines in the noto- and neuropodia of setiger 
<number box="[444,461,1052,1076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2.0">2</number>
; these were replaced by furcate setae from setiger 
<number box="[1027,1041,1052,1076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Blake" box="[1055,1189,1052,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Blake, J. A. (1972) Two new species of polychaetous annelid worms from Baffin Bay and the Davis Strait. Bulletin of the Southern California Academy of Sciences, 71, 127 - 132. Available from: http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 106891 (Accessed 19 Oct. 2015)" type="journal article" year="1972">
Blake 
<number box="[1129,1189,1052,1076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1972.0">1972</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). A re-examination of prepared slides of these spines confirms that these are the same 
<typeStatus box="[860,908,1088,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">type</typeStatus>
of seta reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mackie" box="[1129,1293,1087,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Mackie, A. S. Y. (1991) Scalibregma celticum new species (Polychaeta, Scalibregmatidae) from Europe, with a redescription of Scalibregma inflatum Rathke, 1843 and comments on the genus Sclerobregma Hartman, 1965. Bulletin of Marine Science, 48, 268 - 276." type="journal article" year="1991">
Mackie (
<number box="[1227,1285,1088,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for the three species of 
<taxonomicName box="[268,409,1124,1149]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[268,409,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Scalibregma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
examined by him.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
Following the lead of 
<bibRefCitation author="Mackie" box="[447,615,1159,1184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Mackie, A. S. Y. (1991) Scalibregma celticum new species (Polychaeta, Scalibregmatidae) from Europe, with a redescription of Scalibregma inflatum Rathke, 1843 and comments on the genus Sclerobregma Hartman, 1965. Bulletin of Marine Science, 48, 268 - 276." type="journal article" year="1991">
Mackie (
<number box="[547,607,1160,1184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Blake" box="[627,774,1159,1184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Blake, J. A. (2000) Family Scalibregmatidae Malmgren, 1867. In: Blake, J. A., Hilbig, B. &amp; Scott, P. H. (Eds.), Taxonomic Atlas of the Benthic Fauna of the Santa Maria Basin and the Western Santa Barbara Channel. Santa Barbara Museum of Natural History, Santa Barbara, California, pp. 129 - 144." type="book chapter" year="2000">
Blake (
<number box="[707,766,1160,1184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2000.0">2000</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
examined specimens from California previously identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[188,434,1196,1221]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="inflatum">
<emphasis box="[188,434,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Scalibregma inflatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and described a new species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Blake, 2000" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="2000" box="[811,1148,1196,1221]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="californicum">
<emphasis box="[811,989,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">S. californicum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Blake" box="[1003,1148,1196,1221]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Blake, J. A. (2000) Family Scalibregmatidae Malmgren, 1867. In: Blake, J. A., Hilbig, B. &amp; Scott, P. H. (Eds.), Taxonomic Atlas of the Benthic Fauna of the Santa Maria Basin and the Western Santa Barbara Channel. Santa Barbara Museum of Natural History, Santa Barbara, California, pp. 129 - 144." type="book chapter" year="2000">
Blake, 
<number box="[1088,1148,1196,1220]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. He also suggested that specimens from the 
<collectingCountry box="[391,441,1232,1256]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">U.S.</collectingCountry>
Atlantic coast included at least one new species in addition to 
<taxonomicName box="[1198,1360,1232,1256]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Sclerobregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="stenocerum">
<emphasis box="[1198,1360,1232,1256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">S. stenocerum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Most recently, 
<bibRefCitation box="[254,486,1268,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Bakken, T., Oug, E. &amp; Kongsrud, J. A. (2014) Occurrence and distribution of Pseudoscalibregma and Scalibregma (Annelida, Scalibregmatidae) in the deep Nordic Seas, with the description of Scalibregma hanseni n. sp. Zootaxa, 3753 (2), 101 - 117. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3753.2.1" type="journal article">
Bakken 
<emphasis box="[347,404,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[419,478,1268,1292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="Bakken, Oug &amp; Kongsrud, 2014" authorityName="Bakken, Oug &amp; Kongsrud" authorityYear="2014" box="[609,1100,1268,1293]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hanseni">
<emphasis box="[609,725,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">S. hanseni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bakken" box="[733,1100,1268,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Bakken, T., Oug, E. &amp; Kongsrud, J. A. (2014) Occurrence and distribution of Pseudoscalibregma and Scalibregma (Annelida, Scalibregmatidae) in the deep Nordic Seas, with the description of Scalibregma hanseni n. sp. Zootaxa, 3753 (2), 101 - 117. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3753.2.1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Bakken, Oug &amp; Kongsrud, 
<number box="[1044,1100,1268,1292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from deep water off 
<collectingCountry box="[1341,1433,1269,1293]" name="Norway" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Norway</collectingCountry>
. These authors also focused on the short, spinous setae anterior to normal capillaries in setigers 
<number box="[1267,1309,1304,1328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1â€’2</number>
and found similar spines in 
<taxonomicName authority="Hansen, 1879" authorityName="Hansen" authorityYear="1879" box="[378,910,1340,1365]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Pseudoscalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="parvum">
<emphasis box="[378,703,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Pseudoscalibregma parvum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen" box="[730,902,1340,1364]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Hansen, G. A. (1879) Annelider fra den norske Nordhavsexpedition i 1876. Nyt Magazin for Naturvidenskaern, 24, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1879">
Hansen, 
<number box="[842,902,1340,1364]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1879.0">1879</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. In my own work, numerous species of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,346,1375,1400]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="family">Scalibregmatidae</taxonomicName>
have been examined and these short spinous setae, considered homologous to the lyrate setae, have been found in other genera including some with large curved acicular spines. I now believe that most species of 
<taxonomicName box="[184,379,1447,1472]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="family">Scalibregmatidae</taxonomicName>
having lyrate setae will be found to have the same 
<typeStatus box="[983,1031,1449,1473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">type</typeStatus>
of short spinous setae in segments anterior to where the lyrate setae begin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
To date, specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[449,590,1519,1544]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[449,590,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Scalibregma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[658,762,1519,1544]" name="Antarctica" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Antarctic</collectingCountry>
waters have been identified in several faunal and ecological accounts as 
<taxonomicName box="[290,413,1556,1581]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="inflatum">
<emphasis box="[290,413,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">S. inflatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see reference list below). The only original illustrations of 
<taxonomicName box="[1107,1248,1556,1581]" class="Polychaeta" family="Scalibregmatidae" genus="Scalibregma" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1107,1248,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Scalibregma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1319,1436,1556,1581]" name="Antarctica" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Antarctica</collectingCountry>
appear to be by 
<bibRefCitation author="Knox" box="[349,645,1592,1616]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" refString="Knox, G. A. &amp; Cameron, D. B. (1998) The Marine Fauna of the Ross Sea: Polychaeta. National Institute of Water and Atmospheric Research (NIWA). NIWA Biodiversity Memoir, 108, 1 - 127." type="journal article" year="1998">
Knox &amp; 
<collectingCountry box="[456,559,1592,1616]" name="Cameroon" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Cameron</collectingCountry>
(
<number box="[579,637,1592,1616]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
of the anterior end and a branchiate parapodium from a specimen collected from the Ross Sea in 
<specimenCount box="[499,577,1628,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" type="generic">
<quantity box="[499,573,1628,1653]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.779999999999999" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" unit="m" value="578.0">578 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
